<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1935-12-04T08:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1935-12-04T08:00:00-05:00" n="741" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d741">
                                <note rend="inline" type="source">765.84/2870: Telegram</note>
                                <head>
                                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul at Geneva</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Gilbert</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                            State</gloss>
                                    </hi>
                                </head>
                                <opener>
                                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                                        <placeName>
                                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Geneva</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-12-04T14:00:00+01:00">December 4, 1935—2 p.m.</date>
                                        <lb/> [Received December 4—10:50 a.m.]</dateline>
                                </opener>
                                <p>638. Department’s 141, December 3, 9 a.m. [<hi rend="italic">December 2, 8 p.m.</hi>] and 135, November 21, 2 p.m.;<note n="79" xml:id="d741fn79">Latter not printed.</note>
                                    Consulate’s No. 625, November 29, 2 p.m.; and despatch 1473
                                    (political) October 30.<note n="80" xml:id="d741fn80">Despatch
                                        not printed.</note> I have knowledge that Vasconcellos
                                    derives what he believes to be American policy from unofficial
                                    sources which are in certain aspects definitely misleading. I
                                    thus feel that it might be useful to seek an occasion to call to
                                    his attention Washington’s position as expressed in recent
                                    official statements in a manner similar to that in the case of
                                    Avenol.</p>
                                <p>Please instruct.</p>
                                <closer>
                                    <signed>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Gilbert</hi>
                                    </signed>
                                </closer>
                            </div>
                            </body></text></TEI>